# Copy to .env (or run `make dev`, which writes it for you).
#
# DMOX_ROOT is the host directory that holds the repos DMOX serves docs from
# — typically the parent of this checkout, so its siblings (../podzone,
# ../rust-proxy-handbook, ...) live directly under it. It is bind-mounted
# read-only into the container at /workspaces by
# docker-compose.override.example.yml; DMOX_WORKSPACE_ROOT there points your
# config.yaml's relative source paths at that mount. Compose resolves this
# value relative to the compose file's directory, so ".." means "one level up
# from the repo".
DMOX_ROOT=..
